            'Splash the dolphin had a secret.\n\nDeep inside him, a song had been swimming around for as long as he could remember — a soft, swirling song full of deep water and moonlight and wide open sea. But every time he thought about singing it, his fins went wobbly with shyness.\n\nSo he kept it inside.\n\nHe watched other dolphins leap and spin. He cheered for them quietly. But the song stayed hidden.\n\nThen one dark evening, a great mother whale came through the bay, calling in low, worried rumbles. She had lost her calf in the fog. Every creature listened, but no one knew how to help.\n\nWithout really deciding to, Splash opened his mouth.\n\nThe song came out.\n\nIt rose up through the water and spread across the bay — clear, warm, and reaching. In the distance, a small voice echoed back.\n\nThe calf followed the song home.\n\nThe whale nuzzled Splash gently and said, without words, everything he needed to hear.\n\nThat night, Splash swam home singing his secret song out loud — and found it was no longer secret at all.',
