        description:
            'Sunny the sunflower loved the daytime so much that she absolutely refused to sleep.\n\nWhen the other flowers closed their petals and dozed off, Sunny kept hers wide open, staring up at the stars.\n\n"I don\'t want to miss anything!" she said.\n\nBut after many nights without rest, something went wrong. Her bright yellow petals began to droop. Her green stalk bent. The golden glow that made her beautiful faded to a tired, dusty yellow.\n\nThe old garden — who had seen many seasons come and go — spoke to her gently.\n\n"Dear Sunny. The sun goes to sleep each night so she can rise again more beautifully. The moon rests during the day so she can shine fully at night. Even bees go home to their hive. Rest is not missing out — rest is getting ready."\n\nSunny listened. That evening, for the first time, she folded her petals softly around herself and let her eyes close.\n\nThe next morning, she opened to the sun feeling more alive than she ever had — bright and golden and radiant.\n\n"Ah," she said happily, "so this is what rest feels like."',
