            'Wendy the baby whale had been following her mother through the blue water when a great current swept between them. She spun and tumbled, and when the water was still again, she could not see her mother anywhere.\n\nShe called out — a long, low sound that trembled through the deep.\n\nNo answer.\n\nShe tried again, smaller this time. Her voice sounded so tiny in all that wide ocean.\n\nBut then — a click. A whistle. Two dolphins appeared beside her, bobbing gently. "Come with us," they said.\n\nThey swam with her for a while, and then a sea turtle joined them, calm and steady. Then two older whales came from the deep, humming the ancient songs that whales have sung since the beginning of the sea.\n\nWendy followed the song.\n\nAnd then, far ahead, she heard the sound she had been searching for — her mother\'s voice, calling and calling across the water.\n\nShe swam as fast as her fins could carry her.\n\nWhen her mother wrapped around her in the great warm embrace of a whale, Wendy did not ever want to let go.',
